  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nComparative analysis of two investment strategies: V1 with 1M€ in 10 tranches over 10 years at 0.5% return, versus V2 with 900K€ in 6 tranches over 6 years at 0.5% with crypto reinvestment at 20%. V2 strategy shows superior performance with 2.2M€ additional gain due to crypto leverage effect.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nUser requested financial comparison between two structured investment approaches to determine optimal capital allocation strategy.\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nPerformed detailed financial analysis comparing V1 (conservative 10-year strategy) versus V2 (hybrid strategy with crypto reinvestment), calculating returns, gains, and risk-adjusted performance metrics.\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [financial_analysis] Investment Strategy Comparison — Detailed comparison showing V2 generates 2,207,023€ additional gain\n- [report] Detailed Report with Visualizations — Comprehensive analysis with comparative charts and risk assessment\n\n## Key Decisions & Validations\n\n- V2 strategy identified as superior with 248.33% return vs 2.79% for V1\n- Crypto reinvestment at 20% creates significant temporal leverage advantage\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- Structured tranche approach enables systematic comparison\n- Temporal leverage through early crypto reinvestment highly effective\nDiscoveries:\n\n- V2 strategy generates 80x better performance despite 100K€ less initial investment\n- 20% crypto assumption drives exceptional results but introduces high risk\n\n## Challenges & Blockers\n\n- High dependency on 20% crypto return assumption\n- Significant risk differential between strategies not fully quantified\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- What is acceptable risk tolerance for crypto component?\n- How sensitive are results to crypto return variations?\n- What are optimal hedge strategies for V2 approach?\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Conduct sensitivity analysis on crypto return assumptions\n- Develop risk mitigation strategies for V2 implementation\n- Consider hybrid approaches with risk controls\n---\nUID: dYo24cHZ4Zj7hubS9nFajB | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0128\n"
